parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to lurch forward unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially when merging into traffic or navigating intersections.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck
requires excessive force to depress
or releases suddenly
causing the vehicle to accelerate rapidly. The sticking occurs intermittently
often when starting from a stop
and can happen at any speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potentially cause accidents. Noise from the brakes can be a warning sign of a more serious problem.
symptoms: Frequent replacement of brake pads and rotors
squeaking or groaning noise from the brakes
uneven brake wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake caliper failure can cause extended stopping distance, loss of brake power, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Grinding noise from the brake calipers
extended stopping distance
loss of brake power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure can cause loss of brake power, extended stopping distance, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle fails to stop or slows down unexpectedly
ABS warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Repeated brake repair issues can lead to a loss of trust in the vehicle's braking system, potentially causing accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Frequent visits to the dealer or repair shop for brake repairs
persistent brake problems despite previous repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seat belts to retract properly can lead to a false sense of security, causing occupants to believe they are safely buckled when they are not, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belts do not properly retract after use
leaving 12-18 inches of unretacted seatbelt stuck in the space between the door and door frame
seat belts lock up and will not release
seat belts do not click or unlatch
seat belts will not retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seat belts to release can cause occupants to be trapped in the vehicle, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belts lock up and will not release
seat belts will not click or unlatch
passenger's side seat belt locks while the vehicle is not started.
